parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbags not deploying in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard comes on
the airbag system service is required
the seat detects lightweight objects and gives a warning of seatbelt not on
the airbag light stays on permanently
the airbag sensor beneath the passenger seat is defective.

symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard comes on
the seat detects lightweight objects and gives a warning of seatbelt not on
the airbag sensor beneath the passenger seat is defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or become impossible to drive, leading to accidents or stranding the driver in traffic.
symptoms: The transmission fails prematurely
often between 114
000 miles
causing the vehicle to stall or become difficult to drive. Other symptoms include a high-pitched whining noise
the transmission howling or squealing
the powertrain stopping working
and the vehicle being unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Failure to Engage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or failure to engage can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to drive, leading to accidents or stranding the driver in traffic.
symptoms: The transmission slips or fails to engage
causing the vehicle to stall or become difficult to drive. Other symptoms include the transmission howling or squealing
the powertrain stopping working
and the vehicle being unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A transmission whining or squealing noise can be a sign of premature transmission failure, which can cause the vehicle to stall or become impossible to drive, leading to accidents or stranding the driver in traffic.
symptoms: A high-pitched whining or squealing noise is heard when accelerating above 2000 RPM
often accompanied by other symptoms such as the transmission slipping or failing to engage
the powertrain stopping working
and the vehicle being unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive rust and corrosion can lead to structural failures, compromising the safety of the vehicle and its occupants.
symptoms: Visible rust and corrosion on the subframe crossmember
extreme rust and corrosion on the vehicle's body
possibility of frame coming loose from the body of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A detached lower control arm can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Lower control arm detaches
belt tensioner failure
control module failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear suspension problems can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Rear of the vehicle wobbles while driving
alignment issues
flat spots on tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front suspension problems can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Squeaking noise from the front suspension
oil leakage from the front left strut
uneven suspension response in wet or high-speed conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Parts for Recall Repair (Visibility Issue)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or unavailable parts for the recall repair can lead to frustration and inconvenience for vehicle owners, potentially causing them to delay or forego the necessary repair, which can compromise vehicle safety and visibility.
symptoms: Vehicle owners receive notification of recall but are unable to schedule repair due to part unavailability
dealerships are unable to provide a specific date for part availability
manufacturers are unable to provide an estimated date for repair
and customers are unable to find customer service support for recall repair.
